# <type>(<scope>): <summary>
#
# Types:
#   feat     – new behavior or capability
#   fix      – bug fix
#   refactor – code change that doesn’t add features or fix bugs
#   docs     – documentation or docstrings only
#   test     – tests only
#   build    – makefile, docker, CI, packaging
#   chore    – cleanup, formatting, meta changes
#
# Scope (folder), examples from tome:
#   world, client, db, logging, config, cli, tests, make, docker, docs
#
# Rules:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add", not "added")
#   - Keep the summary under 72 characters
#   - No trailing period
#
# Example:
#   fix(world/map): handle empty room list
#
# Optional body:
#   - Explain intent or reasoning
#   - Mention side effects or follow-ups
